<section>
	<header>
    <h2>Dropdown filters</h2>
	</header>

  <p><strong>Filter dropdowns</strong> bundle checkboxes or radios into a compact panel so users can adjust criteria without leaving the page. Group related options, add a header for context, and keep inputs keyboard-focusable with visible states. For radios, ensure a single selection per group; for checkboxes, consider a clear-all action when lists are long.</p>

	<div class="section-example">
		<div class="dropdown">
			<button>
				Dropdown with filter (checkboxes)
				<svg class="icon last">
					<use xlink:href="/images/icons.svg#chevron-down"></use>
				</svg>
			</button>
			<nav class="panel arrow bottom center">
				<div class="header">Filter title</div>
				<ul class="checkboxes">
					<li>
						<input id="labelOne1" type="checkbox" checked="">
						<label for="labelOne1">Label 1 <small>checked</small></label>
					</li>
					<li>
						<input id="labelTwo1" type="checkbox">
						<label for="labelTwo1">Label 2</label>
					</li>
					<li>
						<input id="labelThree1" type="checkbox">
						<label for="labelThree1">Label 3</label>
					</li>
					<li>
						<input id="labelFour1" type="checkbox">
						<label for="labelFour1">Label 4</label>
					</li>
					<li>
						<input id="labelFive1" type="checkbox">
						<label for="labelFive1">Label 5</label>
					</li>
					<li>
						<input id="labelSix1" type="checkbox">
						<label for="labelSix1">Label 6</label>
					</li>
					<li>
						<input id="labelSeven1" type="checkbox" disabled="">
						<label for="labelSeven1">Label 7 <small>disabled</small></label>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</nav>
		</div>

		<div class="dropdown">
			<button class="primary">
				Dropdown with filter (radio buttons)
				<svg class="icon last">
					<use xlink:href="/images/icons.svg#chevron-down"></use>
				</svg>
